text: Alberto Naranjo [nah-rahn'-ho] (September 14, 1941 – January 27, 2020) was a Venezuelan jazz musician and composer. In 1992, he was nominated for a Grammy Award. Naranjo made arrangements for the groups Conexion Latina, Guaco and Mango; pop-artists like Ilan Chester, Simón Díaz, Oscar D'León, Ricardo Montaner, María Rivas, Aldemaro Romero and Adalberto Santiago ==Discography== * Dulce y Picante *Imagen Latina * Oblación * Swing con Son * El Trabuco Venezolano Vol. I * El Trabuco Venezolano Vol. II * El Trabuco Venezolano Vol. III * El Trabuco Venezolano Vol. IV * El Trabuco Venezolano Vol. V * Irakere & Trabuco, Vol. 1 * Irakere & Trabuco, Vol. 2 * ==References== Category:1941 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Venezuelan composers Category:Jazz musicians Category:People from Caracas
